ready for her, and could ha' been without her stirrup
porredge, though I thanke her for her care. A man can
not be too well prepar'd, or provided for so sweete a
Lady, in so much distresse. A very (^Andromeda^) , chain'd
to a Rock. [$ (^Takes up his Cloak & Sword.^) $]
   [$ (^Nur.^) $] What's this you say? I understand no word of it,
I would take your answer right, though I falter'd in my
Ladies message.
   [$ (^Car.^) $] The Devills in this overruning Tongue of mine,
I could finde in my heart to worme him out with my
