   [$ (^La.^) $] I am his Lordships servant.
   [$ (^Bel.^) $] And I your Lordships good Madam. And yours
Mr. (^Saveall^) .
   [$ (^Sa.^) $] I am for your way Mr. (^Bellamy^) .
   [$ (^Car.^) $] And I sir, and't please you. [$ (^Exit. Sav.       #
Bel.^) $]
   [$ (^La.^) $] (^George Carelesse^) , I would speak with you.
<P D7V>
   [$ (^Car.^) $] May I not wait upon your Gentleman to the 
